text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus kouangsiensis is an uncommon Asian species of trees in the beech family. It has been found only in southern China, in the Provinces of Guangdong, Guangxi, Hunan, and Yunnan.Quercus kouangsiensis is a tree up to 15 meters tall. Leaves can be as much as 20 cm long.
